subject: Add FW Version in journalctl log
commitMessage:
Add FW Version in journalctl log

Adds version logging for AFM and CPLD active and recovery versions as well
as BMC and BIOS recovery versions on every AC cycle and BMC reboot.
Log format: VERSION INFO - <ITEM>_<RECOVERY/ACTIVE> - <version info>
Where <ITEM> is "afm" "bmc", "bios", or "cpld"
and <RECOVERY/ACTIVE> will specify "recovery" or "active" depending on
if the version is the recovery version or the active version,
respectively.
If any version is empty, e.g. "0.0", then it is not printed.
User can retrieve FW versions by running:
journalctl | grep "VERSION INFO"

Tested:
AC Cycle:
VERSION INFO - cpld_active - xx.x-x.x-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
VERSION INFO - bmc_recovery - x.xx-xx-xxxxxxx
VERSION INFO - bios_recovery - x.x
VERSION INFO - cpld_recovery - x.x
VERSION INFO - afm_active - x.x
VERSION INFO - afm_recovery - x.x

BMC reboot:
VERSION INFO - cpld_active - xx.x-x.x-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
VERSION INFO - bmc_recovery - x.xx-xx-xxxxxxx
VERSION INFO - bios_recovery - xxx.xxx
VERSION INFO - cpld_recovery - x.x
VERSION INFO - afm_active - x.x
VERSION INFO - afm_recovery - x.x

Change-Id: I955bc67a9cdc6d53a422d70ee999781cb6e22b08
Signed-off-by: Alex Schendel <alex.schendel@intel.com>

Do we expect users to log into the console and grep through the journal? It's a very poor non-standard interface. We should just make sure these FW versions show up in D-Bus/Redfish and then provide a script to collect the Redfish FirmwareInventory.
This may be a good plan for the future, but the feature request stated that journal logging was expected.

Printing version here means everytime when readCPLDVersion() it gets log in journalctl.

Instead do it in constructor of PfrVersion class..

Was unable to move this to PFRVersion because cpldActive is no longer an ImageType.
Recovery versions have been moved to PFRVersion while cpldActive has been moved to updateCPLDversion() in the mainapp.
Updated packages to include lg2 and am using lg2::info now.

This is good idea, I like it.

Currently PFRManager doesn't maintain BMC active, BIOS active D-Bus objects on this service. Those are maintained in Settings service. Did you added code to print those version as well? If not, That carries major part as most will be looking for BMC/BIOS/CPLD ACTIVE version information than other versions.
BMC active and BIOS active are printed by changes to openbmc-meta-intel and smbios-mdrv2, respectively.
Resolving these long-standing comments that I already addressed.
I don't have a better alternative to suggest here. I will leave it to see if others have some good idea.

This is kind of hardcoding the Type and also missing some component version information. 

You can remove type check here and use directly "path" which will have both information what you are looking for. (Example path: bmc_recovery, bios_recovery etc..) Like Component name ie. BMC/BIOS/CPLD/AFM and Active/recovery). 

https://github.com/openbmc/pfr-manager/blob/master/service/src/mainapp.cpp#L46 ( First arg in tuple is passed as path).

You need to add version print here as well.
Reason: During early BMC boot phase, We don't see full version information, It will be populated on D-Bus with empty string and after some time, it gets updated and populate actual string.

So print version in PfrVersion class constructor change does not fully justice to the requirement. Add print version info here as well. 

Suggestion: You can define a inline function for print version and use in both places.
inline printVersion(const std::string& path, const std::string& version)
